# Plan: Proxy-Pointer RAG findings — three changes, deep dive on #2

## Context

The proxy-pointer-RAG article surfaced three concrete weaknesses in ag's
ingest/retrieval pipeline. We've already audited the actual code at the cited
file/line locations and confirmed each gap. This plan implements all three —
breadcrumb-prefixed embeddings (#1), an entity reconciler shim (#2, the deep
dive), and a `section_id` + `PointerRag` mode (#3) — in the ROI order from the
audit, so the cheapest, highest-value change lands first and the speculative
one lands last.

The pieces are independent at the data layer (different DB columns / graph
properties), but #3 depends on #1's heading stack. Land in order: #1 → #2 → #3.

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph Ingest [Ingest pipeline]
        IR[DocIR blocks] --> CIR["chunk_ir<br/>(memory/chunker_factory.rs)"]
        CIR -->|"text + ChunkMeta{br/>heading_path, section_id}"| EMB[embedder::embed_batch]
        EMB --> IDX["Retriever::index_chunk<br/>(stores text + section_id<br/>in Tantivy)"]
    end

    subgraph Entities [Entity write path]
        IDX --> KB1[index_to_knowledge_graph]
        KB1 --> NER[NER + EntityExtractor]
        NER --> RECON["EntityReconciler<br/>(NEW: embed + cosine + LLM tiebreak)"]
        RECON --> KB2[KnowledgeBuilder::add_entity_mention]
        KB2 --> FDB[(FalkorDB :Entity nodes<br/>+ vecf32 embedding<br/>+ vector index)]
        RECON <-->|"top-k canonical candidates"| FDB
    end

    subgraph Query [Query path]
        Q[User query] --> SR[Retriever::search]
        SR -->|"Vec&lt;String&gt; today"| AG[Agent]
        SR -.->|"NEW: PointerRag asks for<br/>section_ids, then fetch_section"| FS["Retriever::fetch_section<br/>(NEW)"]
        FS -->|"full section text"| AG
    end
```

Change #1 (breadcrumb) prepends `heading_path` to chunk embed text. Change #2
(reconciler) sits between NER and `add_entity_mention`, using FalkorDB's
vector index to find canonical matches. Change #3 (PointerRag) stamps a
`section_id` during chunking, stores it as a Tantivy field, and adds a new
agent mode that fetches sections instead of chunks.

