  - When seeding `pending_meta` (the two existing assignment sites at
    `:96-100`, `:112-116`, `:123-127`), set
    `heading_path: heading_stack.iter().map(|(_, t)| t.clone()).collect()`.
  - The existing behavior of seeding `pending` with the immediate header text
    at `:117-119` stays — but switch it from "just the header" to the full
    breadcrumb (e.g. `AMD > Financial Statements > Cash Flows\n\n`) so the
    embed-side text matches what's in `heading_path`. Use a single
    `format_breadcrumb(&heading_stack)` helper local to the module.
  - `PageBreak` is also `is_strong_boundary()` but is not a header — guard the
    stack mutation on `matches!(block.block_type, BlockType::Header { .. })`.

- `backend/src/index.rs:403-406, 620-621, 764-765` — no signature change;
  `chunk_metas` flows through unchanged, just carries the new field.

- `backend/src/retriever.rs:232` (`doc_id_to_meta: HashMap<String, ChunkMeta>`)
