### Edge cases / failure modes

- **Reconciler down (LLM unreachable, FalkorDB vector index missing)**: fall
  back to today's behavior — `add_entity_mention` with bare lowercase merge.
  Log a one-time warn per doc, increment `reconciler_fallback_total`. Don't
  fail ingest.
- **Vector index creation racing first ingest**: `init_schema` is idempotent;
  call it on app startup as today.
- **Dimension drift** (user swaps embedding model): `db.idx.vector.queryNodes`
  errors on dim mismatch. Surface a warn → fall back. UI work to flag this
  cleanly is out of scope here.
- **Cost cap**: `llm_review_max_per_doc` short-circuits to auto-new once the
  per-document LLM call budget is hit (protects against pathological docs
  with hundreds of borderline-ambiguous entities).
- **Relation-type sprawl** (`link_entities` accepting any string): noted, not
  fixed in this change. The relation-type reconciler is a follow-on with the
  same shape — a small fixed taxonomy + LLM mapping. Out of scope; flag in
  the commit message.

