## #3 — `section_id` + `fetch_section` + `PointerRag` mode (2–3 days)

### Goal
Throw the matched chunk away after retrieval, hydrate the full
heading-bounded section, hand that to the LLM. Useful only because #1
already gives the chunker proper heading awareness.

### Files to modify

- `backend/src/doc_ir.rs:210` — add to `ChunkMeta`:
  ```rust
  pub section_id: String, // UUID per heading-bounded run
  ```

- `backend/src/memory/chunker_factory.rs:66-143` — in `chunk_ir`, generate a
  fresh `Uuid::new_v4().to_string()` whenever the heading stack mutates (i.e.
  on the strong-boundary branch). All chunks accumulated between two
  boundaries share the same `section_id`. Atomic blocks (tables, code) also
  get the current section's id rather than their own.

- `backend/src/retriever.rs` — add a stored Tantivy field. Search for the
  existing field declarations (`title_field`, `content_field`, `doc_id_field`
  near `:230` and the schema-building site) and add `section_id_field` the
  same way. In `add_document` / `index_chunk` (`:880-904`, `:2014-2027`),
  write `meta.section_id` into the field. Add:
  ```rust
  pub fn fetch_section(&self, section_id: &str) -> Result<String, RetrieverError>
  ```
  that runs a Tantivy `TermQuery` on `section_id_field`, sorts results by the
  chunk position (encoded in `doc_id` after `#`), and concatenates the
  contents. Cache key: `format!("section:{}", section_id)` in the existing
  `search_cache` LRU.

- `backend/src/agent.rs:26-41` — add `PointerRag` variant. In
  `run_with_mode` (`:412`), branch on `PointerRag` near the existing
  `AgentMode::Rag` arm at `:594`: do a normal `retriever.search` to get
  top chunks, then for each unique `section_id` (looked up via
  `retriever.meta_for_content` at `:1208`), call `fetch_section`, dedupe,
  hand the sections (rather than the chunks) to the LLM. Cap total tokens
  via existing `MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS` config.

- Tantivy on-disk schema change → existing indices need a rebuild. Two
  options: (a) bump an `INDEX_SCHEMA_VERSION` constant and have startup wipe
  + rebuild if mismatched; (b) make `section_id_field` `OPTIONAL` and treat
  empty as "no section info, fall back to chunk text" so old indices still
  work. Go with (b) — gentler upgrade.

### Tests

- Unit: `fetch_section` returns chunks in `position` order.
- Unit: chunker emits same `section_id` for two chunks under same heading,
  different `section_id` after a header boundary.
- Integration test in `agent.rs` mode-switch suite (look for existing
  `test_agent_mode_*` patterns; add `test_pointer_rag_returns_section_text`).

